Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We propose an exchange rate model that is a hybrid of the conventional specification with monetary fundamentals and the Evans?Lyons microstructure approach. We estimate a model augmented with order flow variables, using a unique data set: almost 100 monthly observations on interdealer order flow on dollar/euro and dollar/yen. The augmented macroeconomic, or ?hybrid,? model exhibits greater in-sample stability and out of sample forecasting improvement vis-à-vis the basic macroeconomic and random walk specifications.
